page.title: 15HORN PARK SCHOOL BIRDSLIST.
page.content: The following birds have been observed in or over the school grounds during the 1960's, 70's and 80's. They indicate the rural aspect of the school, which has much open space nearby, as well as the more normal suburban housing. House sparrow, starling, blackbird, song thrush, feral pigeon, wood pigeon, collard dove, greenfinch, goldfinch robin, pied wagtail, wren,carrion crow magpie, swallow, swift, house martin, kestrel, black-headed gull, herring gull, mallard, wheatear, redwing, fieldfare, blue tit, great tit, long-tailed tit, dunnock, skylark, Observed flying nearby have been Heron, mute swan, Canada goose, lapwing, red-necked parakeet as now found feral in S.E. England.
